AUDD, issued by AUDC Pty Ltd, is a stablecoin pegged to the Australian Dollar (AUD) at a 1:1 ratio, collateralized by cash or cash equivalents held in a bare trust. Introduced in mid-2025, AUDD has gained traction across networks like Ethereum, Stellar, Solana, and Hedera, with its recent expansion to Base announced today. Backed by the Reserve Bank of Australia’s Project Acacia initiative, AUDD supports tokenised asset settlements and interoperability with Australia’s New Payments Platform (NPP). Its transparency is reinforced through regular attestations, reconciling blockchain data with fiat reserves, fostering trust among users.Both stablecoins address the volatility of non-stablecoin cryptocurrencies by offering a stable value tied to their respective national currencies, catering to users who prefer familiarity with local fiat systems.

